<1ST_LINE>r a PM-CrossbowKilling     02-22 0331</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Crossbow Killing,0344</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Fatally Shot With Crossbow</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man awakened by three intruders searching
his apartment for a stolen jacket fatally shot one of them with a
crossbow, authorities said.
   James R. Hucek, 21, was killed after he and his two companions
burst into Tom Hedgecock's apartment early Saturday, according to
Jim Solomons, a spokesman for the Orange County Sheriff's office.
   Gregory M. Farmer and Joseph Roehrick were being held without
bail after being charged with burglary and second-degree murder
under a state law that permits such prosecution for those involved
in a felony resulting in death.
   ``It was pretty traumatic,'' said the 27-year-old Hedgecock, who
was shot in the leg.
   Solomons said Hucek, Roehrick, 22, and Farmer, 25, spotted
Hedgecock's roommate when they were out driving late Friday.
   The three thought that the roommate, Kurt Chaillet, had
something to do with the theft of an expensive leather jacket that
belonged to one of them, Solomons said.
   Chaillet, 25, joined the three for driving and beer drinking and
later took them back to the apartment, where they confronted him
with their suspicions and demanded to search the apartment,
Solomons said.
   The search, which turned up no leather jacket, quickly turned
into a ransacking, and the noise woke Hedgecock, Solomons said.
   ``He told them to get out,'' Solomons said. When they refused,
Hedgecock armed himself with a screwdriver and forced them out.
   He locked and bolted the door, but the three kicked in the door
and pushed their way inside, where Hedgecock had armed himself with
a crossbow.
   He fired once, striking Hucek in the chest and killing him.
   The violence continued as Chaillet ran to call authorities. The
fight between Farmer, Roehrick and Hedgecock moved into the parking
lot, where Roehrick pulled a gun from his truck and shot twice,
hitting Hedgecock in the leg, Solomons said.
   When deputies arrived, they found Farmer and Roehrick in the
parking lot and Hedgecock sitting on his couch.
</TEXT>
