<2ND_LINE>BC-Taiwan-Hijack,0143</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>URGENT
^Plane Hijack Attempt Foiled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hijackers on Monday tried to commandeer a
China Airlines plane carrying 105 passengers on a domestic flight
but were foiled by crew members, officials of the airline reported.
   Officials of China Airlines, Taiwan's official flag carrier,
said the Boeing 737 was en route from Taipei to the southern port
of Kaohsiung, 240 miles away, when the hijack attempt occurred.
   China Airlines officials declined to identify the hijackers, say
how many persons were involved, or provide any additional
information. The said further details would be released at a news
conference later today.
   In 1985, an attempted hijacking occurred aboard a China
Airlines' Boeing 737 flying the same route with 107 passengers. A
homesick army sergeant who wanted to see his parents was
overpowered by crew members after he seized a stewardess.
