<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Argentina-Chauffeur     02-22 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Argentina-Chauffeur,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chauffeur Of Defense Minister Shot To Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chauffeur of Defense Minister
Jose Horacio Jaunarena was shot to death when he tried to prevent a
robbery aboard a bus, police said.
   The chauffeur, Roquelmo Ismael Zapata, 57, was heading home in
the early morning hours when two armed men boarded his bus in
suburban Sarandi and demanded the passengers' money and valuables.
   Police said Zapata produced his .38-caliber handgun, carried as
part of his duties as the defense minister's driver, and a shootout
occurred in which Zapata was wounded several times. No other
casualties were reported, and the gunmen fled, police said.
   Zapata was pronounced dead at Finocchieto Hospital, officials
said.
</TEXT>
