<HEAD>L.L. Bean Heiress Gets Challenger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUGUSTA, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Edward S. ``Ted'' O'Meara, who has a spent
a decade as an aide to members of Maine's congressional delegation,
today launched his own bid for southern Maine's 1st Congressional
District seat.
   ``I have done my apprenticeship with the best and I am ready to
enter the arena as a candidate in my own right,'' he said.
   He will oppose L.L. Bean heiress Linda Bean-Jones for the
Republican nomination. The seat is held by Democratic Rep. Joseph
E. Brennan, a former governor completing his first two-year term.
   O'Meara, 35, worked for Rep. Olympia J. Snowe during her first
term in Congress and joined Sen. William Cohen's staff in 1981. He
is Cohen's executive assistant for Maine, with responsibility for
six offices in the state and a staff of 16 people.
