<HEAD>KAL Bans Smoking On All Domestic Flights</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Korean Airlines announced Monday it
will ban smoking on all domestic flights beginning next month.
   Airline officials said the ban was in line with the worldwide
trend of banning smoking on flights of less than two hours. All of
KAL's domestic flights last less than one hour.
   The action will not affect KAL's international flights, the
officials said.
   Until now, KAL has banned smoking in half of its seats on
domestic flights.
