<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bob Dole's presidential campaign manager said
Monday the Kansas senator intends to take the offensive on the
issue of taxes and may ``start pointing out how many times George
Bush has changed his position'' on the subject.
   Former Sen. Bill Brock also accused the vice president's
campaign of deliberate distortions of Dole's position that were
``demeaning to the political process.''
   Brock made his comments as aides said the campaign had hired new
producers for its television advertisements in the wake of Dole's
defeat by Bush in last week's New Hampshire primary.
   Officials said Michael Murphy and Alex Castellanos, who produced
