<HEAD>Bombs Damage Cars at U.S. Military Base</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GOEPPINGEN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four small bombs exploded in the
parking lot of a U.S. military compound early Monday, damaging
several cars but causing no injuries, police reported.
   They said at least one person climbed the fence around the Cook
Barracks before dawn and set six homemade devices on the ground
beside parked cars, but only four of the bombs went off.
   Police estimated the damage at $2,900. They said no individual
or group claimed responsibility for the attack. U.S. officials did
not comment on the incident.
   Cook Barracks is located on the outskirts of Goeppingen in the
southern state of Baden-Wuerttemberg.
