<HEAD>Philbin Named Acting Chairman Of Federal Maritime Commission</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan on Monday designated Edward
J. Philbin, a former San Diego lawyer and law professor, as acting
chairman of the Federal Maritime Commission.
   Edward V. Hickey Jr., chairman of the commission, died in
January.
   Philbin, 55, has been a member of the commission since 1984.
Before that, he served three years as deputy assistant secretary of
defense for reserve affairs.
   Philbin joined the University of San Diego law faculty in 1970
and became assistant dean in 1973. He was also a partner in a San
Diego law firm specializing in civil litigation.
   He is a member of the Naval Air Reserve and served several tours
of active duty.
