<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--GreatLakesCruise     02-22 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Great Lakes Cruise,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Navy's Annual Great Lakes Cruise To Feature USS Antrim</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The guided-missile frigate USS Antrim has been
selected to steam through the nation's mid-section this year for
the Navy's annual Great Lakes cruise, the service said Monday.
   The cruise, part of the Navy's campaign to recruit sailors, will
send the Antrim to 21 ports over three months.
   ``This annual Navy event ... offers a unique opportunity for
residents of the Great Lakes region to see first-hand a ship from
today's modern Navy,'' the service said.
   The Antrim will begin its cruise with a June 16 stopover at Port
Jefferson, N.Y., the Navy said. Among the larger cities to be
visited are Montreal; Windsor, Ontario; Milwaukee; Chicago; Duluth,
Minn.; Erie, Pa.; Oswego, N.Y., and Toronto.
   The Antrim will end the 1988 cruise in September with stops in
Baltimore and Savannah, Ga., on the way to its homeport in Mayport,
Fla.
</TEXT>
