<TEXT>
   Nothing sends Albert Paul Blaustein
into a lather like being called odd just because he has 1,400 bars
of soap in his basement.
   That's 1,400 catalogued bars from every hotel the 66-year-old
constitutional law scholar has visited in the past 47 years.
   Still, ``I'm not eccentric,'' Blaustein said with good humor in
a recent interview. ``I'd rather be remembered as a nice guy who
did good things for the world.''
