<HEAD>BC-SPE--Taxes and Your Money: Social Security</HEAD>
<HEAD>CORRECTIVE</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDITORS: Members who used b1017 BC-SPE--Taxes: Social Security,
transmitted Jan. 11 under a Washington dateline as part of the
Special Edition on ``Taxes and Your Money,'' are asked to used the
following:</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press, as part of the ``Taxes
and Your Money'' Special Edition, misstated the formula for
determining what portion of Social Security benefits is taxable.
The starting point for the calculation is total income subject to
tax plus half the Social Security benefits.
</TEXT>
