<1ST_LINE>a a BC-SPE--HomeImprovements:Wallpaper     02-22 0108</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-SPE--Home Improvements: Wallpaper,0111</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>BC-SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD>
<HEAD>HOME IMPROVEMENTS: Wallpaper</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY707</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Removing old wallpaper before a refinishing project can be done
quicker and easier with a variable temperature control heat gun.
   Here are some tips from Harry W. Earl, brand manager for Emhart
Corp.'s Thermostrip:
   _ Moisten a section of the old wallpaper with water.
   _ Set the heat gun at full power, holding the nozzle three
inches from the wall and direct the hot air at a seam.
   _ As adhesive begins to soften, gently loosen the paper with a
scraper, then peel off.
   _ Continue moistening the wallpaper throughout the process.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
