<HEAD>South Africa's Inflation Rate Rose</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Africa's inflation rate,
as measured by consumer prices, slipped to 14.2 percent in January
from 14.7 percent in the previous month, the Central Statistical
Services said Monday.
   The government attriubted the improvement to a substantial
decline in food prices.
