<2ND_LINE>BC-Japan-Autos,0089</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Japanese Auto Production Slips In January</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japanese automakers produced fewer cars, trucks and
buses in January over the same period a year ago, the Japan
Automobile Manufacturers' Association said Monday.
   The group said output totaled 918,348 vehicles, down 2 percent
from 1987.
   Last month's decline followed 1.9 percent growth in December,
and breaks a string of five consecutive year-on-year rises.
   A spokesman for the organization said the effects of declining
car exports outweighed continued growth in domestic sales.
</TEXT>
