<HEAD>Korean Air Bans Smoking On All Domestic Flights</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Korean Air said Monday that smoking
will be banned on all domestic flights beginning next month.
   Airline officials said the ban is in line with a worldwide
anti-smoking trend on short-range flights of less than two hours.
All of the carrier's domestic flights last less than one hour.
   The action would not affect Korean Air's international flights.
</TEXT>
