<2ND_LINE>Japan-Markets,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Falls Marginally, Stock Prices Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar fell marginally against the Japanese yen
in early trading Tuesday, while stock prices posted a moderate
advance.
   The dollar opened at 129.27 yen, down 0.68 yen from Monday's
close of 129.95 yen on the Tokyo foreign exchange market.
   Currency dealers said there were no specific incentives
affecting the exchange dealings, but that the dollar remained under
pressure because of Japanese concerns about the U.S. economy.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which rose 73.30 points Monday, gained another
25.71 points or 0.1 percent in early trading, moving to 24,872.42.
</TEXT>
